<HEADLINE> Jiang Zemin Meets Nigerian President Obasanjo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
met here Friday with Nigerian President Olusegun Obasanjo, who are
here to attend the three-day Millennium Summit of the United
Nations which started Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Obasanjo expressed his satisfaction with the development of
relations between the two countries since he took office as
Nigerian President.
</P>
<P>
Obasanjo, who is also current chairman of the Group of 77,
briefed the Chinese leader about the summit meeting of the Group
of 77 in Havana last May, adding that he is grateful for China's
support to the meeting.
</P>
<P>
Obasanjo, who will attend the Sino-African Forum on Cooperation
scheduled for October in Beijing, also expressed his willingness
to further strengthen coordination and cooperation between the
Group of 77 and China.
</P>
<P>
Jiang spoke highly of Nigeria's vigorous efforts in promoting
South-South cooperation and the Group of 77's contribution to the
enhancement of cooperation among the developing countries,
reaffirming China's consistent support for the organization.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that China attaches great importance to developing
relations with Nigeria and hoped that the ties between the two
nations will be further strengthened. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
