<HEADLINE> URGENT: Explosion Occurs in Suburban Urumqi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 9 (Xinhua) -- A catastrophic explosion
occurred Friday evening in suburban Urumqi, capital of west China'
s Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region, with casualties of about 100
people, the Ministry of Public Security announced here today.
</P>
<P>
Sources with the ministry did not give the exact number of
people killed.
</P>
<P>
When traveling on the Xishan Road in the western suburbs of
Urumqi, a vehicle carrying explosives which were planned to be
destroyed suddenly blew up at about 7:30 pm September 8, killing
and injuring people, damaging more than 20 other vehicles and
nearby houses, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
Local police are clearing the spot and rescuing the injured
people. The cause of the explosion is under investigation, the
sources said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
