<HEADLINE> 3 Killed in Road Accident in Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Three Iranian people were killed
Saturday in a collision between two heavy-duty vehicles, the
official IRNA news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The accident took place when a truck, travelling from the
central city of Isfahan to the capital Tehran, sped into the back
of a trailer truck carrying iron bars, according to the report.
</P>
<P>
The collision caused the iron bars to pierce into the driving
cabinet of the trailer truck, killing the driver and two others
sitting beside him.
</P>
<P>
Road accidents have been on the rise in Iran in recent years. A
latest survey showed that some 200,000 highway accidents take place
in the country, leading to some 15,000 deaths. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
