<HEADLINE> Moderate Earthquake Jolts Peru </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, September 9 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake that registered 4.2
degrees on the Richter scale Saturday affected communities in Peru
's three southern departments, but no victims or damage have been
reported, the Peruvian Geophysical Institute (IGP) said.
</P>
<P>
The seismical movement, which occurred at 06:15 local time (11:
15 GMT), was located 40 kilometers northeast of Moguegua, at a
depth of 22 kilometers.
</P>
<P>
According to the Institute, the tremor was felt also in
Arequipa and Tacna, a city on the border with Chile.
</P>
<P>
This is the second earthquake felt in Peru in the last 24 hours,
after one recorded Friday in communities of the Piura department,
in the north of the country.
</P>
<P>
The other movement of 4.5 degrees on the Richter scale neither
caused victims nor material damage. 
</P>
</TEXT>
