<DOCNO> XIE20000909.0013 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Italy Urges EU to Build Federal Police Force </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Italian Interior Minister Enzo
Bianco Saturday put his weight behind plans for a federal police
force in the European Union (EU) and a European prosecutor's
office.
</P>
<P>
In a speech to the first pan-European conference of anti-Mafia
prosecutors opened on Friday in Italian northern city of Caserta,
he said crime organizations now have a "supra-national matrix and
dimensions".
</P>
<P>
The EU nations are already on the path to closer police
cooperation and the creation of what is called a "common juridical
space" involving a prosecutor's office and common norms for some
crimes, but some have been reluctant to consider even that, let
alone anything more extensive.
</P>
<P>
"In time, we must arrive at a full-fledged federal police force
to combat crime with a supra-national dimension," Bianco proposed.
</P>
<P>
"To get results, one must move in step with a European
juridical space, the common norms for some crimes and a European
prosecutor's office," he added.
</P>
<P>
The pan-European conference of anti-Mafia prosecutors will end
Sunday in Caserta. 
</P>
</TEXT>
