<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UAE Hopes to End High Oil Prices </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, September 9 (Xinhua) -- The United Arab Emirates, one
of the world major oil producers and exporters, has expressed the
wish for cooperation between consuming and producing countries in
order to put an end to high prices of petroleum.
</P>
<P>
Obeid bin Saif Al Nasir, minister of petroleum and mineral
resources, made the statement before his departure Saturday for
Vienna to participate in Sunday's meeting of the Organization of
Petroleum Exporting Countries.
</P>
<P>
According to the official WAM news agency, the meeting will
discuss the issue of increasing the organization's production quota
to put an end to the increase in oil prices and to appoint a new
secretary for the oil cartel.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, arrangements being made for holding an OPEC summit in
Venezuela by the end of this month will also be discussed during
the meeting.
</P>
<P>
However, Nasir described the Vienna meeting as an ordinary one,
which will only tackle the situation in the oil market. 
</P>
</TEXT>
