<HEADLINE> Vice-Premier Attends Concert Commemorating Late Musician </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Vice-Premier Li Lanqing
attended tonight the concert marking the 60th anniversary of the
birth of late Chinese musician Shi Guangnan at Beijing's Zhongshan
Concert Hall.
</P>
<P>
The concert will feature the most outstanding music pieces
composed by the musician, including the "Toast Fytte," one of the
most widely known songs composed by Shi hailing the victory
against the "Gang of Four" in 1976.
</P>
<P>
Various Chinese singers who are well-known for singing songs
composed by Shi will sing at the concert, which was held both on
September 8 and 9.
</P>
<P>
Shi, born in Chongqing Municipality in August 1940, died of a
heart attack at his piano on May 2, 1990.
</P>
<P>
As former vice-chairman of the Chinese Musicians' Association,
Shi composed more than 100 music pieces during his 20 year career.
</P>
