<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vietnam to Export 160,000 Cubic Meters of Wood </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Vietnamese government decided to
use 160,000 cubic meters of wood to make wooden products for
export this year, Vietnam News Agency reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Under the decision, which was signed by Deputy Prime Minister
Nguyen Cong Tan, about 300,000 cubic meters of wood will be logged
from natural forests in 2000 and the volume will be maintained
annually for the next ten years.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam currently has 19.03 million hectares (ha) of forest. Of
the total acreage, 8.25 million ha are covered with natural
forests and 1.05 million ha, with plantations.
</P>
<P>
Natural forests shrink by between 70,000 ha and 80,000 ha every
year, threatening the habitats of many forest animals. Only nine
percent of natural forests are capable of yielding an average 150
cubic meters of wood per ha; 33 percent, 80-150 cubic meters of
wood; and the rest, very little.
</P>
<P>
To preserve and develop natural forests, Vietnamese government
has controlled their exploitation and has tended to close them off.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
