<HEADLINE> Today's Diplomatic News Highlights </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 9 (Xinhua)-- Following are highlights of
today's diplomatic news released by Xinhua:
</P>
<P>
Chinese Premier Meets U.S. Guests
</P>
<P>
Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji met today with Former U.S. Secretary
of Treasury Robert Rubin and his party in the capital city of
northwest China's Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
Zhu briefed the guests on the Chinese government's policies in
developing the western area, the natural resources in Xinjiang,
and China's reforms and opening up.
</P>
<P>
The premier also exchanged views with the guests on China-U.S.
cooperation in securities, finance, and investment.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Premier Meets Japanese Delegation
</P>
<P>
Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji met with a delegation with the Japan-
China Association on Economy and Trade headed by its President
Sugiichiro Watari in this capital of Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous
Region in west China today.
</P>
<P>
Zhu highly appreciated the long-term efforts of the association
in promoting economic and trade relations between China and Japan
and expressed the hope that Japanese enterprises would develop
more cooperation in China's western regions.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Vice-Premier Meets Thai Deputy PM
</P>
<P>
Chinese Vice-Premier Li Lanqing met today with Thai Deputy
Prime Minister Supachai Panitchpakdi.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, the two leaders discussed ways of promoting
Sino-Thai economic and trade cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Chinese, Irish Deputy PMs Discuss Relations
</P>
<P>
Sino-Irish relations have been developing well, and China is
confident of the growth of such relations.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Vice-Premier Li Lanqing made the remarks in talks with
Mary Harney, deputy prime minister and minister for Enterprise,
Trade and Employment of Ireland, Friday. 
</P>
