<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Investigation Into Three Gorges Tragedy Begins </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YICHANG, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Chinese commodities inspection
authorities and technical experts from the U.S. Rotec Co., the
supplier of the tower belt machine that killed three workers,
today began tests on the accident at the Three Gorges Project.
</P>
<P>
Together with the Rotec technicians, the Chinese experts will
analyze the base material, the solder, and other equipment to
ascertain the cause of the accident.
</P>
<P>
Around 6:50 pm on September 3, workers from Gezhouba Company
Group were still working at the flood discharge section of the
gigantic water control dam when the No. 3 tower belt machine broke
from a height of 19.6 meters and collapsed, throwing down 29
workers who were working on the belt. Four other workers that were
working under the tower were injured.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. company sent its representative Barry Crouchman to
join the investigation team.
</P>
<P>
Authoritative sources said Gezhouba Group Company has banned
the use of other tower belt machines and roof belt machines.
Concrete pouring at the flood discharge section has been put on
hold. 
</P>
</TEXT>
