<HEADLINE> Chinese Traditional Enterprise Invests in Genetic Medical Sector </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, September 9 (Xinhua) -- The Changzhou Diesel Engine
Company Ltd., the world's largest producer of medium and low-
powered diesel engines, bought 33 percent of the stock shares of
the Nanjing Yilai Genetic Medicine Company Ltd today.
</P>
<P>
Both of the companies are located in east China's Jiangsu
Province. Today's purchase was valued at 29 million yuan (3.5
million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Changzhou Diesel Engine Company Ltd, with a history of over 80
years, has an annual output of 1.8 million sets of diesel engines.
The company will invest in the information and biotechnology
sectors.
</P>
<P>
A leader of the traditional enterprise said that the company
plans to purchase a number of large pharmaceutical manufacturers
and medical service organs in the future to set up a comprehensive
medical industry network. 
</P>
