<HEADLINE> United States Beats Australia in Men's Basketball Warmup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SYDNEY, September 9 (Xinhua) -- The United States NBA side
defeated the Australian team 89-64 in a men's basketball warmup in
Melbourne on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The American Dream Team led 34-27 at half-time before 14,000
spectators.
</P>
<P>
The friendly was barely minutes old when Australian captain
Andrew Gaze, who had taken a three-point shot, dragged American
Vince Carter to the floor to prevent him from a breakaway basket.
</P>
<P>
With Carter standing menacingly over Gaze, players from both
teams came charging in with Australian Shane Heal screaming abuse
at Carter and shaping up to the NBA star in scenes.
</P>
<P>
The match referees struggled to keep the players apart.
