MACAO, September 9 (Xinhua) -- China's Macao Special
Administrative Region (SAR) and Ministry of Health signed five
agreements here Saturday to strengthen medical cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The agreements cover the training of medical workers for Macao,
medical exchanges and the invitation of inland specialists to
Macao.
</P>
<P>
The agreements were signed by those in charge of government
medical departments and medical institutions both in the country's
inland areas and Macao.
</P>
