<HEADLINE> Cambodia Holds Seminar on Khmer Language </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Some 100 linguist scholars
from deferent areas of the country ended Saturday a three-day
seminar on discussion of the standardization and promotion of the
Khmer language.
</P>
<P>
It is the first time for Cambodian scholars to meet and discuss
the common standard of the Khmer language since 1975 .
</P>
<P>
Tol Lah, minister of education expressed the hope at the
seminar that the standardization of the language will serve the
interest of the people.
</P>
<P>
Cambodia's dictionary was first introduced officially by
Buddhist patriarch Chuon Nath in 1915, which accomplishes with
about 18,000 entries.
</P>
<P>
The seminar also reached a consensus on the creation of new
dictionary which contains 10,000 to 30,000 new words.
</P>
<P>
Besides, the seminar has focused on a new standard way to use
Khmer characters on the computer. 
</P>
</TEXT>
