<HEADLINE> Ugandan Army Captures Rebel Commander </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, September 9 (Xinhua) -- The Ugandan army has captured
a rebel commander and killed four others in ambushes in western
Uganda, Army Spokesman Phinehas Katirima confirmed Saturday.
</P>
<P>
According to the spokesman, an Allied Democratic Forces (ADF)
commander, identified as Isa Lubega alias, was captured in an
ambush in Mubende district at dawn on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Lubega has been the director of operations of the ADF rebels in
Mubende district.
</P>
<P>
The Uganda People's Defense Forces is currently involved in a
major clean-up exercise of rebel elements in the country, mainly
in northern and western Uganda, Katirima said, disclosing that the
army have so far captured 12 ADF rebels since the beginning of
September.
</P>
<P>
Ugandan President Yoweri Museveni Thursday vowed to root out
all ADF rebels who disturbed civilians in the west of the country.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a rally during his visit to Hoima district where
rebels are rampant, Museveni called on the population to be on the
look-out and report all suspicious activities to the appropriate
authorities.
</P>
<P>
He urged security organs to respond promptly to every
information passed on to them by the people concerning rebel
movements and activities in the areas. 
