<HEADLINE> Road Accident Kills 8 in Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Eight people were killed on
Friday in a traffic accident in Iran's northeastern province of
Khorasan, the Islamic Republic News Agency reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Traffic police of the province said the accident happened on the
road linking the Qouchan city and provincial capital Mashhad when a
pick-up collided with a jeep running on the opposite side.
</P>
<P>
The collision occurred when the pick-up suddenly swerved to the
left.
</P>
<P>
Road accidents are on the rise in Iran. Traffic experts believe
that the narrow roads, heavy traffic and non-observation of traffic
rules by drivers are the main reasons for deadly accidents.
</P>
<P>
A recent survey conducted in this regard revealed that some 200,
000 accidents take place on Iranian highways each year, resulting
in the death of 15,000 people. 
