<HEADLINE> Zambia to Act Against Casualizing Labor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, September 9 (Xinhua) -- The Zambian government will
soon act against companies, especially foreign investors, over
casualizing labor in an attempt to avoid meeting certain
conditions of service, Zambia Daily Mail newspaper reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
The newspaper quoted Zambia's Acting Labor and Social Security
Minister Newstead Zimba as saying here Thursday that the
government is concerned about the casualization of labor and is
following up the matter.
</P>
<P>
Some employers, especially foreign investors, are engaging
workers on short-term contracts in order to avoid dispensing their
legal obligations such as payment of housing allowance, leave pay
and other benefits, he said.
</P>
<P>
He said the government will formulate policy objectives which
will take into account the internal and external factors to
conform to the current social and economic environment. 
