<HEADLINE> 35 Feared Drowned in Indian Boat Capsize </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 9 (Xinhua) -- At least 35 people were
feared drowned when a boat carrying them capsized midstream in a
rain-swollen river in north India's Uttar Pradesh state on
Thursday, the Press Trust of India (PTI) said in an overnight
report.
</P>
<P>
The boat was ferrying over 40 people when it sank in Peelakhar
river in Rampur district of Uttar Pradesh, the PTI quoted local
police as saying.
</P>
<P>
Only five people swam to safety and the rest were missing and
presumed dead, the police added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
