<HEADLINE> Chile To Present Swordfish Case Against EU </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Chile and the European Union,
the latter representing the Spanish fishing fleet, will present
their cases in the swordfish dispute before the High Seas Court on
September 14 in Hamburg, Germany, an official of the Chilean
Foreign Ministry said on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Assistant Foreign Minister Heraldo Munoz said Chile will submit
additional documents to strengthen its position on refusing
Spanish fishing vessels access to Chilean ports to unload and re-
ship swordfish catches.
</P>
<P>
Chile, which first banned the vessels in 1991 in order to
protect the rare fish, says that allowing them would violate
Chile's restriction on harvesting the fish.
</P>
<P>
Munoz said a meeting is likely to be held late this month as
part of the parallel World Trade Organization process to resolve
the dispute. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
