<HEADLINE> New Sony Subsidiary in Wuxi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 9 (Xinhua)-- The Japanese Sony Corporation
will set up a new company this month in Wuxi city in east China's
Jiangsu Province, with an initial investment of 23 million U.S.
dollars.
</P>
<P>
The Sony Electronics (Wuxi) Ltd, a wholly owned company of Sony
(China) Ltd, is expected to start producing lithium ion polymer
rechargeable batteries and other mobile phone equipment in April
2001 at the monthly production capacity of two million units,
according to today's China Daily.
</P>
<P>
The thin and lightweight batteries developed by Sony are used
for mobile phones and other devices such as digital video cameras
and notebook PCs.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, mobile phones have been increasingly popular
in the world. By the end of May this year, there were about 36.9
million mobile phone users in China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
