<HEADLINE> APEC Finance Ministers Meeting Opens in Brunei </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Bandaer Seri Begawan, September 9 (Xinhua) -- The 7th meeting
of finance ministers of the 21 APEC member economies opened here
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The ministers are scheduled to discuss global and regional
developments in both the macroeconomic and financial fields,
progress in reforming the international financial architecture,
multilateral efforts in developing international financial
standards and codes as well as strengthening financial systems.
</P>
<P>
The minister will also discuss special directives from APEC
leaders on how to pursue greater links between APEC fora and their
work programs and on dealing with financial market issues, various
collaborative initiatives already under way and several proposals
for new initiatives.
</P>
<P>
They will hold discussions with the three international
financial institutions, namely the International Monetary Fund,
World Bank and Asian Development Bank.
</P>
<P>
The ministers will also meet with representatives of the APEC
Financiers Group, the APEC Business Advisory Council, and the
Pacific Economic Cooperation Council.
</P>
<P>
During the two-day meeting, China, as the next host of the APEC
Finance Minister Meeting, will brief the ministers on the
arrangements for the meeting in Suzhou, East China, next year.
</P>
</TEXT>
