<DOCNO> XIE20000909.0176 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Panama Seizes Shipment of Weapons </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SAN JOSE, September 8 (Xinhua) -- A shipment of weapons
including AK-47 automatic rifles, grenade launchers, explosives
and ammunition was seized by Panamanian authorities on Wednesday,
Public Security sources said on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Nine people -- six Colombians, two Panamanians, and a
Venezuelan -- were arrested.
</P>
<P>
The seizure includes 271 AK-47 automatic rifles, 318 RPG-7
grenade launchers, 13 hand grenades, 99 M-203 mortar grenades, 1,
273 kilograms of explosives, mortar launchers, a rocket launcher
and other kinds of ammunition.
</P>
<P>
The weapons were hidden in a truck which crossed the Costa Rica-
Panama border on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
On Thursday, an operation aimed at finding more weapons was
carried out on the road connecting the two countries, but no
seizure was reported.
</P>
<P>
Police said an AK-47 automatic rifle can be sold for 2,000 U.S.
dollars in black markets. Some groups of drug traffickers exchange
weapons for drugs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
