<HEADLINE> King of Jordan to Visit Canada </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, September 8 (Xinhua) -- King Abdullah Bin Al-Hussein of
Jordan will pay a working visit to Ottawa on September 11-12,
Canadian Prime Minister Jean Chretien announced Friday.
</P>
<P>
The king will be accompanied by a high-level delegation
composed of Prince Ali Bin Al-Hussein, Prime Minister Ali Abu
Ragheb, Chief of the Royal Hashemite Court Fayez Tarawneh, Deputy
Prime Minister Mohammad Halalqa and Foreign Affairs Minister Abdul
IIah Khatib.
</P>
<P>
"His Majesty's visit to Ottawa, so soon after my own visit to
Jordan this past April, is evidence of the growing relations
between our two countries," Chretien said.
</P>
<P>
He stressed Canada's world class information technology as the
key sector for the Jordanian government's interest, "as the
Kingdom expands its infrastructure and modernizes its economy."
</P>
<P>
During the visit, officials of the two countries will discuss
bilateral trade and the Middle East peace process, according to a
Canadian government's announcement. 
</P>
</TEXT>
