<HEADLINE> Colombia Air Force Destroys Arms-Smuggling Plane </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BOGOTA, September 8 (Xinhua) -- The Colombian Air Force (FAC)
Friday destroyed a plane with a load of weapons it carried from
overseas for rebels, said FAC Commander General Hector Fabio
Velasco.
</P>
<P>
The aircraft was destroyed on a landing strip of Buenos Aires,
a remote border area of the departments of Guainia, Guavire and
Meta in southeastern Colombia, he said.
</P>
<P>
"The plane had as its destination the zone of distention in the
south of the country," said the officer, adding the cargo was for
the Revolutionary Armed Forces of Colombia (FARC), said the
officer.
</P>
<P>
"We know that it brought a cargo of weapons. These are planes
that make trips taking out drug and bring in weapons," Velasco
told local reporters.
</P>
<P>
The people aboard the plane, whose nationality has not yet been
confirmed, abandoned the plane in a hurry before the FAC
destroyed it.
</P>
<P>
The FAC destroyed another aircraft loaded with weapons for FARC
on Tuesday on a landing strip near Barrancominas, also close to
the demilitarized zone, said Velasco. 
</P>
