<HEADLINE> Fire-hit Ore-dressing Plant Resumes Production </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, September 9 (Xinhua) -- The Dashan Ore-dressing Plant
under the Dexing Copper Mine in east China's Jiangxi Province,
which was hit by a big fire on September 4, resumed production
today.
</P>
<P>
All of the plant's eight ball mills went into operation this
morning, local sources said.
</P>
<P>
The plant was hit by a big fire caused by an electric failure
in the central control-room on the afternoon of September 4. The
fire destroyed part of the equipment in the central control-room
and caused a direct economic loss of 900,000 yuan. No casualties
were reported in the accident.
</P>
<P>
The Jiangxi Copper Co., the superior organ of the Dashan Ore-
dressing Plant, is China's first non-ferrous metals firm listed
overseas and one of the country's largest enterprises which
combines mining, ore-dressing, smelting and processing. It is the
biggest copper production base in China and the 13th in the world.
</P>
<P>
The Dashan Ore-dressing Plant, the largest of its kind in China,
has a daily ore-dressing capacity of 60,000 tons.  
</P>
</TEXT>
