will ask their Russian counterparts to extradite three members of
an international arms trafficking group allegedly headed by former
Peruvian army lieutenant Jose Luis Aybar Cancho, Peruvian judicial
sources said Friday.
</P>
<P>
Celinda Segura Salas, the judge in charge of a case concerning
arms trafficking from Jordan, announced that she would request the
Russian government to extradite Ana Doris, Astrih, and Brihani
from the same Aybar Cancho family, who are involved "in this
criminal act."
</P>
<P>
The arms trafficking group had already sold some 10,000
Kalashnikov rifles to guerrillas of the Revolutionary Armed Forces
of Colombia, said the sources.
</P>
<P>
Official procedures will be carried out soon to facilitate the
extradition, said the sources.
</P>
<P>
Investigations carried out by the First Prosecutor Office show
that the 45-year-old Ana Doris Aybar Cancho, who is on the run in
Russia, is the contact person of the arms smuggling organization
with its partners in Croatia, Russia, the United States and
Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
Peruvian police said they know little about Astrih and Brichani.
</P>
