<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Panama's National Maritime
Service patrol officers, police and Drug Prosecutor Office agents
confiscated 90 kilograms of drugs dumped into the sea in less than
a month, according to official sources on Friday.
</P>
<P>
They said 20 people were detained during the operation.
</P>
<P>
The authorities explained that drugs had been dropped from
light planes by drug traffickers, most of them Colombians, at
night and were to be recovered afterwards by Panamanian drug
traffickers. The drugs, hidden in fuel tanks of vehicles, would be
smuggled via Central America to the United States.
</P>
<P>
The authorities said the trucks which carry drugs to the
Central American countries often return with weapons for the
Colombian paramilitary and guerrillas. 
