the gold medal in his event.
</P>
<P>
Curtis Frye, coach of American rival Allen Johnson, is
confident that his 110m title holder will return to form and
upstage his Welsh rival at the Olympics.
</P>
<P>
Johnson, who did not compete in Brussels and Gateshead in
August after injuring his hamstring while training for an expected
showdown with world champion Jackson in Monaco.
</P>
<P>
