<HEADLINE> Motorcycle-rider to Conquer Mount Everest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, September 9 (Xinhua)-- Chen Jianguo, a local citizen
in this capital city of Jiangsu Province in east China, will ride
a motorcycle to climb up Mount Everest in southwest China.
</P>
<P>
He left Nanjing Monday for Tibet and will arrive at the
mountain on September 14. Chen is confident that he can create a
new record of climbing up to 6,800 meters.
</P>
<P>
Chen practiced by riding up the mountain at the height of 5,600
meters in April.
</P>
<P>
Chen Jianguo began his vehicle training career when he was 14
years old and has covered a distance of more than 100,000 km. so
far.
</P>
<P>
Last year, he rode across the Taklimakan desert in southwest
China's Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region, known as the "Sea of
Death", which earned him a place in the Guinness Book of Records.
</P>
