<HEADLINE> Government Support Drives Shandong's Export Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, September 9 (Xinhua)-- The export value of machinery and
electrical equipment in east China's Shandong Province reached 610
million U.S. dollars in the first half year, up 74 percent from
the same period last year, latest statistics show.
</P>
<P>
Preferential treatment by local government on technological
development, equipment introduction, loans guarantee and material
import have all contributed to the rapid export growth, local
official sources said.
</P>
<P>
In the first half of the year, local machinery and electrical
equipment producers have got more than 800 million yuan (over 96
million U.S dollars) of loans from central and provincial
governments.
</P>
<P>
Shandong also organized trade fairs with United Arab Emirates
and Taiwan which brought abundant export contracts and 15 million
U.S. dollars contractual capital to local enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Shandong will focus on supporting backbone enterprises to build
up ten export industrial bases, which include the sectors of
household appliances, vehicle accessories, ships and watches.
</P>
