<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pakistan to Intensify Campaign Against Drug Traffickers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, September 8 (Xinhua) -- The Pakistani government
decided here Friday to intensify campaign against drug-trafficking
by air, by using all possible means including use of detecting
machines, snuffer dogs and a coordinated and well-knit
intelligence system.
</P>
<P>
This was decided at a meeting presided over by Interior
Minister Moinuddin Haider, according to the Associated Press of
Pakistan (APP).
</P>
<P>
Moinuddin Haider told the meeting that the world has
appreciated and acknowledged Pakistan's efforts against narcotics.
</P>
<P>
"We have successfully controlled and reduced poppy cultivation
to a great extent besides being able to destroy a large number of
heroine laboratories," he added.
</P>
<P>
He remarked that there is need to concentrate more on drug-
trafficking from Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
Moinuddin lamented that a number of drug traffickers with
Pakistani passports are arrested in the Gulf States and other
parts of the world which brings a bad name to the country.
</P>
<P>
This situation, he said, must be immediately arrested and
strict and concrete efforts be made in this connection.
</P>
<P>
It was decided that the Foreign Office will instruct Pakistani
missions abroad to provide all available information about those
arrested in their respective states to the concerned agencies in
Pakistan, so that it can be analyzed and utilized in busting the
gangs involved in drug-trafficking.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, law enforcing and other co-agencies are asked to make
arrangements which can be contacted and can co-act for the purpose.
</P>
<P>
Moinuddin Haider instructed the authorities to make sure that
the warning system for the drug-peddlers is strengthened and taken
to a high-key, so that traffickers are time and again reminded
that penalty for the offense was as strict as death in some
countries of the world. 
</P>
</TEXT>
