<HEADLINE> Pakistani Exports Record 790 Million Dollars in August </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan's exports during
August were recorded at 790 million U.S. dollars, showing an
increase of 23.6 percent as against 639 million dollars in the
corresponding period of last year, the Associated Press of
Pakistan (APP) reported.
</P>
<P>
In achieving this, the highest ever in August, the country's
exports also exceeded the target of 783 million dollars, set for
the second month of this fiscal beginning July 1, 2000, APP quoted
official statistics here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
However, on the year-to-date basis, the target for July-August
2000 was 1,525 million dollars and the actual exports stood at 1,
459 million dollars, showing a shortfall of 67 million dollars
during the first two months of the current fiscal.
</P>
<P>
The export trends have facilitated reduction in the trade
deficit as well.
</P>
<P>
During the first two months of the current fiscal, the trade
deficit came down to 313 million dollars as compared to 375.6
million dollars of the corresponding period of last fiscal,
registering an improvement of 16.7 percent despite higher import
growth of 9.6 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
