<HEADLINE> Williams, Davenport Make All-American Final in US Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Venus Williams prevailed over
Martina Hingis on Friday to set up an all-American U.S. Open
women's final against Lindsay Davenport.
</P>
<P>
Williams, the third-seeded Wimbledon champion, battled back
from 3-5 down in the third set to pull out a 4-6, 6-3, 7-5 triumph.
</P>
<P>
"We gave the crowd a great show," said top seed and 1997 Open
champion Hingis, who has not won a Grand Slam title since the 1999
Australian Open.
</P>
<P>
The victory extended Williams's winning streak to 25 matches
and kept Hingis from reaching her fourth consecutive U.S. Open
final.
</P>
<P>
Hingis will surrender her world number one ranking to Davenport
the second seed captures her second U.S. Open crown.
</P>
<P>
Davenport, the 1998 Open winner and reigning Australian Open
champion, scored a 6-2, 7-6 victory over unseeded 18-year-old
Russian Elena Dementieva, a Grand Slam semifinal debutante.
</P>
<P>
It was Davenport who spoiled the possibility of an all-Williams
final with her impressive straight sets dismantling of defending
champion Serena Williams. 
</P>
