<HEADLINE> British Cyclist Banned for One Year for Doping </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 8 (Xinhua) -- British cyclist Neil Campbell
was banned for one year after being found guilty of a drug offense
on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Thus, Campbell was excluded from the British Olympic squad.
</P>
<P>
Campbell, 26, tested positive at a World Cup track meeting in
Turin, Italy, on July 13 and at the British Championships on July
29. Both samples eventually showed higher concentrations of human
chorionic gonadotrophin (HCG).
</P>
<P>
He was sent home two weeks ago from the Olympic training camp
in Australia, said The Daily Telegraph.
</P>
<P>
World Anti-Doping Agency secretary general Harry Salvasamy said
10 or 11 cases have been reported to date since the organization
began conducting unannounced tests in April. 
