<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Homemade Helicopter to Be Used in Civil Aviation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, September 9 (Xinhua) -- China's homemade helicopters
will be used for the first time in civil aviation after it went
through a high-standard airworthiness flight test recently.
</P>
<P>
The test, called "flying on the verge of death", requires the
aircraft to undergo high-risk flight trials.
</P>
<P>
Experts say that the aircraft created a breakthrough in China's
airworthiness flight test.
</P>
<P>
The helicopter has created several records during the trial
flight, with flight duration of five hours at normal temperature,
a two-hour flight at 38 degrees Celsius below zero and a
temperature difference between 6 degrees Centigrade and 43 degrees
Centigrade minus. It also managed 1,332 km fault-free flight.
</P>
<P>
The manufacture of the helicopter began in 1991 by Changhe
Company in Jindezhen of east China's Jiangxi Province. It is able
to fly 598 km at a speed of 240 km per hour.
</P>
<P>
The helicopter can be used for many purposes, such as coaching,
reconnaissance, communication, rescue, smuggle suppression and
scientific research.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
