<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Southwest China Develops Tourism Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Tourism has become an
important industry in China's southwestern regions, according to
an interprovincial conference on economic development held
recently in southwest China's Chongqing Municipality.
</P>
<P>
Southwest China's Yunnan Province will further develop its
domestic and international tourism market by opening more key
tourist routes.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government will join hands with neighboring
provinces and regions to promote local tourism resources and build
tourist facilities.
</P>
<P>
Yunnan Province hosted the Kunming International Horticulture
Expo last year. The Expo increased the tourism value of Yunnan by
20 billion yuan (2.4 billion US dollars).
</P>
<P>
The international media predicts that the Tibet Autonomous
Region will be one of the world's hottest tourism destinations in
the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
The newly opened direct flight from the German city of Munich
to southwest China's Chongqing Municipality will bring more
European tourists to China.
</P>
<P>
The route provides the quickest and the most economical way for
European tourists to directly enter China's hinterland. After
arrival in Chongqing, European tourists are able to take part in
more than 20 tourism programs across the country.
</P>
<P>
This will break the traditional tourism route, in which
European tourists first visit eastern China before traveling to
western China.
</P>
<P>
Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region and the provinces of Sichuan,
Yunnan and Guizhou have signed agreements on further cooperation
in the tourism industry. They will share tourism resources and
jointly develop a series of tourism programs to major scenic spots.
</P>
<P>
Tourism development in the region will concentrate on
traditional sightseeing, exploration tours, recreational vacations,
exposition visits and participation in scientific projects.
</P>
</TEXT>
