<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hughes Network Finds Chinese Partner for DirecPC </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Hughes Network System (HNS)
under the U.S. satellite giant, Hughes Facilities, has teamed up
with a Chinese electronic company to jointly adapt its patented
personal computer, DirecPC, for the Chinese market.
</P>
<P>
Under an agreement signed between the HNS and Nanning Shengli
Electronic Holding Co., the first batch of DirecPCs will be seen
on the local market before the end of this year.
</P>
<P>
Hughes Network System will provide production facilities and
key technology for the Shengli Electronic Holding Co. to develop
the Chinese version of the computer program to be installed on
computers sold in China.
</P>
<P>
The DirecPC computer depends on satellites for data
transmission, which can increase the Internet browsing speed to
400 KB per second and the document transmission speed to 3 MB per
second. It has made bulk audio and video transfers possible at a
high speed and low cost. 
</P>
