<TEXT>
<P>
BOGOTA, September 9 (Xinhua) -- A Revolutionary Armed Forces of
Colombia (FARC) urban faction blew up a gas pipeline of the state
oil company in the Barrancabermeja river port and caused a big
fire, regional police authorities said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The terrorist attack occurred Saturday in a sector of Colombia'
s northeastern port town, where the Colombian Oil Company
ECOPETROL has its main industrial complex.
</P>
<P>
The Barrancabermeja police operative commander Colonel Jaime
Eduardo Martinez told the press that the attack caused the
spilling of hundreds of barrels of fuel and a fire with flames 30
meters high.
</P>
<P>
The fire was threatening two neighborhoods, but it was
controlled after several hours of work of the fire brigades,
company technicians and policemen, Martinez said.
</P>
<P>
The police chief attributed the attack to an urban faction of
the main guerrilla of the country, the FARC, saying that the
authorities have not determined what kind of explosive the rebels
used. 
